West led the \C5, which looks like a fourth-best from length, so I win the \CA and take charge. Trumps need only the king knocked out, so I drive it and draw the rest. Then I work the spades: AKQ cash, and a fourth round removes the outstanding J and T, leaving my fifth spade good. Trumps give me the entry back to cash that promoted spade, and my running count comfortably reaches and exceeds ten.

[ROLE declarer][STAGE post-play]
