I have reached 4\H and need ten tricks. My spades are headed by AKQJ9 and cash freely, and I also have the \HA and \CA \CK. The trump suit itself is the suit to establish: QJT95 facing my ace is missing only the king, and leading trumps to drive that king out turns the rest of the suit into winners. I might think about finessing the king instead, but my ace and dummy's QJT9 sit in opposite hands, so no lead can trap it — if I lead the queen, a careful East simply declines to cover and keeps the king to score later. Since the king has to make a trick whatever I do, the finesse gains nothing here; I just drive it out and lose at most that one trump. The plan is to lead trumps, knock out the king, and let the long hearts run, using my spade and club entries as needed.

